Trygar: <br>
use trygar to make a wall with the pylofuf boots combo and stall to draw many cards, he can last awhile due to his high energize, when he is defeated place out a pylofuf or tunnel hyren, or if none available just throw out something<br>
Gogor: <br>
Use the main setup of the two tunnel hyrens to make everything burrowed, use gravel storm every turn to wipe out enemys creatures.<br>
Sorrowing ogar:<br>
Never really gets to her but if she does it will hurt core. Lots of core presence where i play so she helps out a bunch.<br>
Warriors Boots/Ormagon- the ultimate combo for creature and magi destruction<br>
Hubram- to retrive any spell needed when you can use it again<br>
Urhail- lets you play those dream rifts for creature recycling and drawing extra cards<br>
Jore- awsome when he is burrowed with the tunnel hyrens adds energy to every other creature that is burrowed<br>
Crystal Jile/mushroom hyren- used when you need energy in a pinch <br>
Amulet of ombor- i know what you are all thinking but when you add 2-4 energy to a burrowed creature its mean.<br>
Hidden door- get those precious relics<br>
Thats about it but it still needs to be lessened in cards and needs a few more duplicates but i don&#39;t have them yet. </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000"> </Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">DeckTech <BR> For the Players, By the Players  <BR>www.decktech.net </FONT></TD></TR></table> 
